PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1781111161
OL,3,CEngland legend Paul Gascoigne holds
OL,4,Cback tears as he discusses addiction
OL,6,FGascoigne said he simply tries to take
OL,7,Fthings one day at a time, adding: "I
OL,8,Fdon't try and think weeks ahead
OL,9,Fbecause I don't know about tomorrow.
OL,10,FAll I know is I'm safe today.
OL,12,F"It used to be a battle every time I
OL,13,Fwoke up. A big battle. But now it's
OL,14,Feasy. I get up, I have a coffee, I
OL,15,Fwork out what I'm going to do that day
OL,16,Fand I plan the day ahead."
OL,18,FGascoigne reflected on his time at the
OL,19,F1990s World Cup as "one of the best
OL,20,Ftimes I've ever had in my life",
OL,21,Fadding: "I loved it."
